snippet.textDisplay: Absolutely brilliant music this game has. Really helps the atmosphere. Individual pieces like this one really don't do it justice, but this is certainly one to remember.
snippet.textOriginal: Absolutely brilliant music this game has. Really helps the atmosphere. Individual pieces like this one really don't do it justice, but this is certainly one to remember.

snippet.textDisplay: @Koopsas There's nothing illogical about the puzzles and they make perfect sense. And if you can't figure them out you can use the arcade answer system, to help you if you're stuck but I don't see how this is a "flawed hint system," unless you mean that it tells you how to solve the puzzle. This is not a hard game by any stretch and is worth more than just a look.
snippet.textOriginal: @Koopsas There's nothing illogical about the puzzles and they make perfect sense. And if you can't figure them out you can use the arcade answer system, to help you if you're stuck but I don't see how this is a "flawed hint system," unless you mean that it tells you how to solve the puzzle. snippet.textDisplay: Machinarium is a game of two halfs, one half is the beauty of the hand drawn art, making this game one of the best looking games this decade, follwed by the perfectly arranged soundtrack, which fits the mood of the game like a glove. (any one who like this should look at this " Machinarium Soundtrack 06 - Mr. Handagote (Tomas Dvorak)" The other half is comprisesd of illlodgical puzzles, that only make scence half the time, further hindered by a flawed hint system. But it is still worth a look.

snippet.textDisplay: Machinarium is such an awesome game! I picked it up as soon as I tried the demo, it was so much fun, going back to the old school style point and click adventures. Beautiful artwork and a fun story. My favorite track from the game is "The Sea", an ABSOLUTELY FANTASTIC ambient piece. I encourage everyone here to check out that track, as well as the game.
